	(74,1,'2015-04-07 01:12:52','2015-04-07 01:12:52','Law Week Colorado is the state’s only newspaper published<strong> specifically for lawyers, law firms, corporate counsel</strong>, and the judiciary. Written and edited by award-winning journalists who have credibility in the legal marketplace, Law Week Colorado is the paper of record for Denver’s 10th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals.\r\n\r\nThe online version, LawWeekOnline.com, is the <strong>state’s leading independent portal for legal news and information</strong>, pushing daily e-mail bulletins and Twitter alerts to thousands of subscribers. Visitors also benefit from content selected from the Law Week newspaper, original web-only stories and video, as well as useful links to similar publications.\r\n\r\nThoughtful and informative, readers respect the independent voice of Law Week Colorado and LawWeekOnline.com and consider it an <strong>essential tool in successful business/client development.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Advertising</strong> in Law Week Colorado and on LawWeekOnline.com provides a <strong>targeted and economical way</strong> to promote your company’s brand awareness, image or message. Our sponsorship opportunities afford access to key decision makers in the industry. Personalized account management and customized design services make the advertising experience simple and rewarding.\r\n\r\n<strong>Fast Facts</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Each week, Law Week Colorado is distributed to over <strong>1,500 corporate counsel and district judges</strong> within the state.</li>\r\n	<li>Law Week Colorado is read by over <strong>15,000 readers weekly</strong></li>\r\n	<li>We reach the <strong>top 200 firms</strong> in Colorado</li>\r\n	<li>LawWeekOnline.com <strong>averages 22,000 visitors a month</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Our <strong>daily e-news</strong> is distributed to over 1,000 subscribers a day</li>\r\n	<li><strong>94% </strong>of readers believe Law Week is relevant to their profession</li>\r\n</ul>','Law Week Colorado','','publish','closed','closed','','law-week-colorado','','','2015-04-13 22:14:33','2015-04-13 22:14:33','',0,'http://localhost:8888/Jhorton_CircuitMedia/?post_type=products&#038;p=74',0,'products','',0),
	(75,1,'2015-04-07 01:13:28','2015-04-07 01:13:28','State Bill Colorado is a robust news and information website covering Colorado’s General Assembly. Our secure legislative tracking service provides the fastest and most complete data available.\r\n\r\nReceive information about all introduced legislation, including bill summaries, sponsor and committee calendars. Review the entire bill on your smart phone or iPad in PDF or other flexible formats. Receive alerts through State Bill or through your social media applications for updates.\r\n\r\nTraining and technical support is complimentary with a paid subscription.','State Bill Colorado','','publish','closed','closed','','state-bill','','','2015-04-13 22:18:35','2015-04-13 22:18:35','',0,'http://localhost:8888/Jhorton_CircuitMedia/?post_type=products&#038;p=75',0,'products','',0),
	(76,1,'2015-04-07 01:13:39','2015-04-07 01:13:39','The 2014 Colorado Legislative Gold Book is all new for the General Assembly’s Second Regular Session!\r\n\r\nOur annual, pocket-sized guide features 82 pages of biographies and pictures of every representative and senator. The Goldbook also includes detailed information on committee assignments, and contact information for virtually all Capitol staff.\r\n\r\nThe guide is available for delivery.\r\n\r\nShop for Gold Books  here.','Gold Book','','publish','closed','closed','','gold-book','','','2015-04-13 22:13:45','2015-04-13 22:13:45','',0,'http://localhost:8888/Jhorton_CircuitMedia/?post_type=products&#038;p=76',0,'products','',0),
	(77,1,'2015-04-07 01:14:01','2015-04-07 01:14:01','Mobile CRS 2014 provides easy and affordable access on your mobile device and tablet to all titles, articles, and sections of the Colorado Revised Statutes, as amended.\r\n\r\nThe current version reflects the official version of the statutes for 2014 with changes passed at the Second Regular Session of the 69th General Assembly. Mobile CRS 2014 supplements all 44 of your physical volumes of the statutes and is a perfect companion for your “on-the-go” reference needs.\r\n\r\nTop features of the app include:\r\n\r\n• The ability to reach all 30,000+ sections of the Colorado Revised Statutes with no Internet connection required;\r\n• Full keyword search of the text;\r\n• Ability to add notes and bookmarks to sections as well as to email sections and notes;\r\n• Quickly delete all bookmarked sections;\r\n• View all notes at once, and send email backups of all notes at once.\r\n\r\nIf you enjoy using Mobile CRS 2014, please consider leaving positive feedback in the app store. If you have difficulties using the application, please let us know at support@comlabmobile.com.\r\n\r\nThis product is produced in partnership with <a href=\"http://mobilecrs.wordpress.com/\">COM-LABS</a>.','Digital CRS','','publish','closed','closed','','digital-crs','','','2015-04-13 22:13:19','2015-04-13 22:13:19','',0,'http://localhost:8888/Jhorton_CircuitMedia/?post_type=products&#038;p=77',0,'products','',0),
